 Martin Jeffrey, operations manager at Emer-G-Med, confirmed the incident and said they received the call at approximately 05:30 that there was an accident involving two vehicles and a truck.  “However, on our arrival we found that there was no truck involved, and that it was a head-on collision between two Isuzu double cab bakkies.” Five people were stabilised and treated by Emer-G-Med and ER24 on the scene. Three of the patients received priority support while two patients were given advanced life support due to the nature of their head injuries. ALSO READ: Five tourists injured after head on collision  The patients were then transported to Themba Hospital and Kiaat Private Hospital. The cause of
the accident is not yet known, but the police were on the scene to establish it.